1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,360
[Characters, behaviors, places,
organizations, and events shown in the series

2
00:00:02,400 --> 00:00:04,800
are entirely fictional,
are solely for entertainment purposes,

3
00:00:04,840 --> 00:00:07,820
with no intention to instruct
or promote any kind of behavior;

4
00:00:07,860 --> 00:00:10,040
viewer discretion is advised]

5
00:00:10,760 --> 00:00:12,120
Right now,

6
00:00:12,280 --> 00:00:14,080
Z has less than a week left.

7
00:00:14,200 --> 00:00:15,600
I'd like to warn you.

8
00:00:16,480 --> 00:00:18,600
If there's something you want to do,
just go for it,

9
00:00:18,920 --> 00:00:23,440
I don't know
how much time we have left,

10
00:00:24,920 --> 00:00:26,560
but right at this moment,

11
00:00:27,160 --> 00:00:28,680
we're officially together.

12
00:00:28,880 --> 00:00:29,880
Beam!

13
00:00:32,200 --> 00:00:34,200
I shouldn't have brought you to see Bew.

14
00:00:35,840 --> 00:00:37,040
You're my daughter.

15
00:00:37,880 --> 00:00:39,560
My only daughter.

16
00:01:21,400 --> 00:01:23,120
I shouldn't have told her.

17
00:01:25,320 --> 00:01:27,039
I really shouldn't have.

18
00:01:33,840 --> 00:01:35,000
I think...

19
00:01:36,000 --> 00:01:37,240
it's good that you did.

20
00:01:37,720 --> 00:01:39,000
At least,

21
00:01:40,160 --> 00:01:41,759
Z finally knows the truth.

22
00:01:44,200 --> 00:01:46,000
When I had Beam,

23
00:01:47,800 --> 00:01:49,479
I was so terrified

24
00:01:50,460 --> 00:01:52,080
that the world would condemn me,

25
00:01:52,960 --> 00:01:55,840
that my fans would hate me
and wouldn't understand me.

26
00:01:56,759 --> 00:01:59,280
I valued those people

27
00:02:00,940 --> 00:02:02,920
without thinking about my own child.

28
00:02:12,720 --> 00:02:14,640
I'm the worst mother.

29
00:02:19,280 --> 00:02:21,160
If I could turn back time,

30
00:02:21,980 --> 00:02:23,680
I wouldn't have made that decision.

31
00:02:26,160 --> 00:02:27,840
I want a chance to take it all back.

32
00:03:08,480 --> 00:03:09,760
I'm sad, Jane.

33
00:03:13,160 --> 00:03:15,680
I'm sad that
I didn't treasure my own life.

34
00:03:18,480 --> 00:03:19,560
It's ironic, huh?

35
00:03:21,840 --> 00:03:23,760
I wanted nothing more than to die.

36
00:03:28,070 --> 00:03:29,990
But now that I'm dying to be back,

37
00:03:35,520 --> 00:03:37,600
there's nothing I can do.

38
00:03:47,200 --> 00:03:48,600
It's gonna be fine...

39
00:06:17,600 --> 00:06:18,480
Z?

40
00:06:20,360 --> 00:06:21,280
What's up?

41
00:06:25,320 --> 00:06:26,160
Wait...

42
00:06:28,080 --> 00:06:29,360
I have to call you Beam from now on.

43
00:06:33,260 --> 00:06:34,800
Just call me Z like before.

44
00:06:41,920 --> 00:06:43,080
I think that...

45
00:06:45,760 --> 00:06:47,080
the time you have left...

46
00:06:52,120 --> 00:06:54,080
You should spend it with your family.

47
00:06:58,880 --> 00:07:00,060
What do you mean?

48
00:07:02,960 --> 00:07:03,960
Well...

49
00:07:11,200 --> 00:07:12,520
After this,

50
00:07:14,880 --> 00:07:16,400
please move in with your family.

51
00:08:28,390 --> 00:08:30,390
[Auntie Bew]

52
00:08:58,720 --> 00:08:59,920
Do you need something?

53
00:09:09,680 --> 00:09:12,520
From now on, I'm someone
who will be by your side

54
00:09:12,560 --> 00:09:13,640
for a week, Miss Jane.

55
00:09:13,920 --> 00:09:14,760
Huh?!

56
00:09:20,880 --> 00:09:22,320
Hello, Auntie Bew?

57
00:09:23,000 --> 00:09:24,240
What is it, Jane?

58
00:09:24,680 --> 00:09:25,600
Auntie Bew,

59
00:09:25,640 --> 00:09:27,280
is Z over at your place?

60
00:09:29,120 --> 00:09:31,120
No, I haven't seen anyone visit.

61
00:09:32,840 --> 00:09:33,640
Oh...

62
00:09:36,360 --> 00:09:37,240
Okay, then.

63
00:09:41,880 --> 00:09:46,080
"Because of the severe violation
committed by Angel No. Z328,

64
00:09:46,120 --> 00:09:47,760
it has been decided
that she be substituted."

65
00:09:47,880 --> 00:09:48,720
Huh?!

66
00:09:49,620 --> 00:09:50,440
Wait!

67
00:09:53,400 --> 00:09:54,120
Wait...

68
00:09:55,640 --> 00:09:56,280
Uh...

69
00:09:57,000 --> 00:09:59,080
So...

70
00:10:00,000 --> 00:10:02,600
Where should I start, Miss Jane?

71
00:10:02,840 --> 00:10:04,200
Just say the word.

72
00:10:04,400 --> 00:10:05,680
I can do everything.

73
00:10:05,720 --> 00:10:06,800
Tell me!

74
00:10:08,520 --> 00:10:09,520
Please go back.

75
00:10:09,560 --> 00:10:10,760
I don't need anyone else.

76
00:10:10,920 --> 00:10:12,640
I want no one but Z.

77
00:10:19,400 --> 00:10:20,400
Miss Jane!

78
00:10:22,000 --> 00:10:22,920
Get out!

79
00:10:30,480 --> 00:10:32,240
Excuse me? Can you give me a ride?

80
00:10:45,000 --> 00:10:46,240
What are you in for?

81
00:10:49,120 --> 00:10:50,720
I secretly visited my family.

82
00:10:52,080 --> 00:10:52,960
You did?

83
00:10:53,600 --> 00:10:55,040
Talking about skills!

84
00:10:55,320 --> 00:10:56,560
How did you figure out where they were?

85
00:10:58,160 --> 00:10:59,370
It's a long story.

86
00:11:04,080 --> 00:11:06,560
Angel No. R664,

87
00:11:06,780 --> 00:11:09,760
please prepare
for your sentencing hearing.

88
00:11:11,040 --> 00:11:13,400
It's always angel this, angel that.

89
00:11:14,240 --> 00:11:15,560
Look at the state we're in.

90
00:11:17,120 --> 00:11:18,040
That's true.

91
00:11:19,520 --> 00:11:21,880
What angels only face misery?

92
00:11:22,920 --> 00:11:23,920
You want my take?

93
00:11:26,280 --> 00:11:27,680
We're no angels.

94
00:11:30,000 --> 00:11:31,280
We're just...

95
00:11:32,320 --> 00:11:33,920
wandering spirits...

96
00:11:36,640 --> 00:11:38,580
who were gone too soon.

97
00:11:41,040 --> 00:11:42,600
We had no business dying so fucking early.

98
00:11:44,020 --> 00:11:45,520
Angels, my ass.

99
00:11:45,800 --> 00:11:47,080
I'm in a fucking jail.

100
00:11:50,670 --> 00:11:51,880
You're quite a hottie.

101
00:12:04,760 --> 00:12:06,120
Ugh, Jane...

102
00:12:08,680 --> 00:12:11,120
You've been sitting
in my bar for three days now.

103
00:12:12,440 --> 00:12:14,360
I won't be cleaning up
your vomit this time.

104
00:12:15,320 --> 00:12:16,480
Why not?!

105
00:12:16,600 --> 00:12:17,920
I'm mourning here!

106
00:12:18,880 --> 00:12:19,760
We can tell, sweetie.

107
00:12:19,800 --> 00:12:21,600
I finally had a girlfriend,

108
00:12:21,640 --> 00:12:23,000
but she disappeared

109
00:12:23,040 --> 00:12:25,800
after two days together...

110
00:12:26,400 --> 00:12:27,800
That's so sad.

111
00:12:28,200 --> 00:12:29,920
When I asked for her back in the app,

112
00:12:30,160 --> 00:12:31,640
she wouldn't come!

113
00:12:33,480 --> 00:12:34,600
What the actual fuck?

114
00:12:34,800 --> 00:12:38,520
Look, it's saying, "Unable to proceed"!
[Angel No. Z328 is unavailable]

115
00:12:38,560 --> 00:12:39,480
See?!

116
00:12:40,000 --> 00:12:41,240
- Do you see this?!
- Yep, I do.

117
00:12:41,280 --> 00:12:42,680
- Do you see this?!
- Yes, sweetie.

118
00:12:42,720 --> 00:12:43,920
Ugh!

119
00:12:45,280 --> 00:12:47,160
You were being sensible the other day,

120
00:12:47,360 --> 00:12:48,920
saying you'd do good deeds every day

121
00:12:49,140 --> 00:12:50,760
to keep her with you forever.

122
00:12:50,800 --> 00:12:53,120
All of a sudden,
you end up drinking like there's no tomorrow.

123
00:12:54,040 --> 00:12:54,760
Alright.

124
00:12:59,800 --> 00:13:01,000
This is not gonna fly.

125
00:13:01,240 --> 00:13:02,560
We need to distract her.

126
00:13:05,960 --> 00:13:06,960
Hey,

127
00:13:07,220 --> 00:13:10,480
if we get everything all packed

128
00:13:10,520 --> 00:13:13,400
and actually donate them to flood victims,

129
00:13:13,640 --> 00:13:15,160
just maybe,

130
00:13:15,200 --> 00:13:18,400
your merit points
will shoot up to a thousand!

131
00:13:19,640 --> 00:13:20,400
True.

132
00:13:21,920 --> 00:13:24,680
But if you keep up
with that gloomy attitude,

133
00:13:24,840 --> 00:13:26,360
even three days won't be enough

134
00:13:26,600 --> 00:13:28,080
for you to finish these.

135
00:13:28,120 --> 00:13:28,880
Right on.

136
00:13:31,200 --> 00:13:32,840
Well, my heart is gloomy.

137
00:13:33,400 --> 00:13:34,480
How about...

138
00:13:34,880 --> 00:13:37,800
you think of this
as saving up for a wedding?

139
00:13:38,480 --> 00:13:39,480
- Good call!
- Exactly!

140
00:13:39,640 --> 00:13:40,280
Huh?

141
00:13:40,760 --> 00:13:44,240
Collect merit points
like you're saving up for a wedding.

142
00:13:44,820 --> 00:13:48,320
You never know
when or if you'll get married,

143
00:13:48,820 --> 00:13:50,240
but if you go hard on it,

144
00:13:50,280 --> 00:13:52,600
you can be wifed up
the minute you're ready!

145
00:13:52,720 --> 00:13:53,720
- Yup!
- Yup!!

146
00:13:53,920 --> 00:13:55,640
Saving up for a wedding...

147
00:13:55,680 --> 00:13:57,040
- Yup!!
- Yup!

148
00:13:59,640 --> 00:14:00,320
Hey!

149
00:14:02,740 --> 00:14:03,680
I do want a wedding!

150
00:14:03,720 --> 00:14:05,760
That's my girl!

151
00:14:07,680 --> 00:14:08,280
Put it in.

152
00:14:08,320 --> 00:14:11,130
Time to earn some merit points!

153
00:14:18,160 --> 00:14:20,720
We're finally done. I'm all drained now.

154
00:14:22,560 --> 00:14:23,400
Do you think...

155
00:14:24,360 --> 00:14:26,400
the people
who receive these will be happy?

156
00:14:27,280 --> 00:14:28,960
- Of course.
- She put in a lot of effort.

157
00:14:29,280 --> 00:14:29,880
I'm gonna do some laundry.

158
00:14:29,920 --> 00:14:30,600
Here.

159
00:14:32,000 --> 00:14:33,080
What is this?

160
00:14:33,120 --> 00:14:34,280
Why don't you find out?

161
00:14:40,800 --> 00:14:42,480
Ta-da!

162
00:14:42,520 --> 00:14:44,520
Wow!

163
00:14:44,560 --> 00:14:45,960
Whoa!!

164
00:14:47,520 --> 00:14:49,080
Thank you so much, guys!

165
00:14:51,200 --> 00:14:53,520
Cuddle her all you want

166
00:14:53,560 --> 00:14:54,720
so that you're not a sad blob.

167
00:14:57,520 --> 00:14:59,160
I just know you'll hold her 24/7.

168
00:15:08,800 --> 00:15:09,720
Hello?

169
00:15:11,000 --> 00:15:11,720
Huh?!

170
00:15:12,400 --> 00:15:13,400
Are you serious?!

171
00:15:16,280 --> 00:15:17,580
Thank you so much!

172
00:15:19,420 --> 00:15:20,420
- Hey!
- What is it?

173
00:15:21,480 --> 00:15:22,480
Finally,

174
00:15:22,800 --> 00:15:24,320
I have a physical store I could rent!

175
00:15:24,360 --> 00:15:25,600
- Eek!
- Argh!!

176
00:15:27,880 --> 00:15:30,930
- Yay! Totally fab!
- Yay!

177
00:15:31,640 --> 00:15:32,640
Congrats, girl!

178
00:15:33,360 --> 00:15:35,480
I'll finally have my own shio pan shop!

179
00:15:35,520 --> 00:15:37,200
- Yay!
- You killed it!

180
00:15:37,240 --> 00:15:38,240
You killed it!

181
00:15:38,680 --> 00:15:40,640
Alrighty, welcome in!

182
00:15:41,000 --> 00:15:45,040
Welcome to JenZ Shio Pan!

183
00:15:46,560 --> 00:15:49,400
Hello. Right now,
there's a buy-one-get-two-free deal.

184
00:15:50,840 --> 00:15:52,200
This, this, and this.

185
00:15:52,240 --> 00:15:54,320
You already paid? Oh, you scanned to pay?

186
00:15:54,640 --> 00:15:55,520
Alright!

187
00:15:57,640 --> 00:15:58,560
Bushy!

188
00:15:58,960 --> 00:15:59,720
Alrighty!

189
00:15:59,920 --> 00:16:00,760
Go right ahead.

190
00:16:01,320 --> 00:16:02,720
Right, okay. For that...

191
00:16:02,760 --> 00:16:03,760
Here you go.

192
00:16:05,800 --> 00:16:07,770
It's you!

193
00:16:07,810 --> 00:16:08,660
Gorgeous.

194
00:16:22,040 --> 00:16:23,400
Next up is this one.

195
00:16:27,600 --> 00:16:28,400
Alright.

196
00:16:28,440 --> 00:16:30,400
- I'll scan to pay.
- Go ahead right here.

197
00:16:30,440 --> 00:16:31,400
Sure. Just a moment.

198
00:16:31,440 --> 00:16:32,440
Jane!

199
00:16:33,560 --> 00:16:34,240
Come on.

200
00:16:36,320 --> 00:16:39,000
Your order is served.
Just like a snap of a finger, huh?

201
00:16:39,640 --> 00:16:42,120
Here you go. Enjoy your bread.

202
00:16:51,600 --> 00:16:53,480
I'm so shattered!

203
00:16:53,640 --> 00:16:54,480
Hey,

204
00:16:54,760 --> 00:16:56,960
our liquor bar is not
as crowded as this, don't you think?

205
00:16:57,160 --> 00:16:59,520
I'm so far from
being used to this many people!

206
00:16:59,800 --> 00:17:01,040
Girl, you're not bad at all.

207
00:17:01,240 --> 00:17:03,320
It's the first day,
and you already devoured that sales target!

208
00:17:03,360 --> 00:17:04,520
Ugh,

209
00:17:04,680 --> 00:17:06,240
like that was impossible to achieve.

210
00:17:06,359 --> 00:17:08,400
Who'd be bold enough
to run a buy-one-get-two-free deal?

211
00:17:08,560 --> 00:17:10,040
It's like you're afraid you'll get rich.

212
00:17:10,200 --> 00:17:11,319
Is being bankrupt on your list?

213
00:17:11,520 --> 00:17:13,160
What?!

214
00:17:13,359 --> 00:17:14,880
At least, there are customers!

215
00:17:14,920 --> 00:17:17,359
- Sure, sure.
- That alone makes me happy.

216
00:17:19,200 --> 00:17:20,319
- Good on you, girl.
- True.

217
00:17:20,599 --> 00:17:21,680
I can't do this every day, though.

218
00:17:22,319 --> 00:17:23,079
It's exhausting.

219
00:17:25,700 --> 00:17:26,760
I'll check up on the bread.

220
00:17:29,800 --> 00:17:30,560
Girls.

221
00:17:31,440 --> 00:17:32,200
- What's up?
- What?

222
00:17:33,080 --> 00:17:34,080
She smiles,

223
00:17:34,480 --> 00:17:35,880
but it doesn't reach her eyes.

224
00:17:37,160 --> 00:17:37,920
Right?

225
00:17:38,280 --> 00:17:40,920
Seeing this makes me feel so bad for her.

226
00:17:41,240 --> 00:17:41,950
Totally.

227
00:17:42,500 --> 00:17:44,680
She was always a bright girl.

228
00:18:06,960 --> 00:18:07,960
Today,

229
00:18:09,200 --> 00:18:10,800
I finally opened my own physical store.

230
00:18:17,880 --> 00:18:20,960
May this place
achieve great sales every day.

231
00:18:24,000 --> 00:18:24,800
Abracadabra!

232
00:18:41,600 --> 00:18:42,400
All set!

233
00:18:48,440 --> 00:18:50,440
Ugh, what is happening?!

234
00:18:50,480 --> 00:18:53,360
It's 2 P.M.
without a single customer all day?

235
00:19:06,020 --> 00:19:09,750
Please come back and help me, baby.

236
00:19:23,480 --> 00:19:24,800
Hello, A-Mah.

237
00:19:25,160 --> 00:19:26,360
Hello, Uncle.

238
00:19:29,280 --> 00:19:31,760
What happened to your arm, A-Mah?

239
00:19:32,240 --> 00:19:35,160
She fell from a ladder
while trimming branches

240
00:19:35,520 --> 00:19:37,000
and broke her arm.

241
00:19:37,440 --> 00:19:38,960
- Oh...
- Mm.

242
00:19:39,120 --> 00:19:41,040
Alright, I'll leave her to you.

243
00:19:41,400 --> 00:19:42,960
- Huh?!
- We've got our hands full at home today.

244
00:19:43,220 --> 00:19:45,120
I myself have to rush to a meeting.

245
00:19:45,760 --> 00:19:47,880
- What...
- I'll pick her up late in the evening.

246
00:19:47,920 --> 00:19:49,040
Uh, what... What?

247
00:19:49,080 --> 00:19:50,880
- I have to go.
- But I have to...

248
00:20:06,360 --> 00:20:08,320
A-Mah, this is from a good restaurant.

249
00:20:13,360 --> 00:20:14,200
Here,

250
00:20:14,240 --> 00:20:15,400
have a bite so that you have some energy.

251
00:20:16,160 --> 00:20:18,040
What?

252
00:20:19,720 --> 00:20:20,440
Bingo!

253
00:20:22,360 --> 00:20:23,840
♫A-Mah, nom-nom♫

254
00:20:23,880 --> 00:20:25,200
♫Nom-nom, nom-nom♫

255
00:20:32,600 --> 00:20:34,600
Come om, A-Mah.

256
00:20:35,220 --> 00:20:36,220
Just a bite.

257
00:20:37,020 --> 00:20:38,320
You won't heal if you don't eat.

258
00:20:41,080 --> 00:20:41,800
Quick.

259
00:20:45,800 --> 00:20:47,320
Good job!

260
00:20:47,640 --> 00:20:48,640
Is that good, A-Mah?

261
00:20:49,480 --> 00:20:51,800
See? Told you so.

262
00:20:52,040 --> 00:20:54,360
This restaurant is fire.

263
00:20:58,180 --> 00:20:59,060
Let's have a bite of pork.

264
00:21:05,600 --> 00:21:06,760
That's also yummy, right?

265
00:22:07,300 --> 00:22:08,360
Good morning!

266
00:22:08,400 --> 00:22:10,520
Let's say hi to this bright morning.

267
00:22:10,560 --> 00:22:12,280
If you happen to pass by,
[Day 1]

268
00:22:12,320 --> 00:22:14,640
don't forget to pay a visit!

269
00:22:18,720 --> 00:22:20,320
Ooh, we've got a customer.

270
00:22:20,360 --> 00:22:21,240
Give me a sec.

271
00:22:21,680 --> 00:22:23,720
Hello! What can I get you today?

272
00:22:24,560 --> 00:22:26,480
I'll take one each.

273
00:22:26,640 --> 00:22:28,280
Alrighty, please give me a moment.

274
00:22:30,080 --> 00:22:30,760
One each...

275
00:22:30,800 --> 00:22:32,480
Thank you so much!

276
00:22:32,960 --> 00:22:34,800
Enjoy your bread!

277
00:22:41,480 --> 00:22:42,560
How was that, A-Mah?

278
00:22:42,800 --> 00:22:43,800
Did I do great?

279
00:22:46,560 --> 00:22:48,560
[Day 2]

280
00:22:48,740 --> 00:22:51,600
Alright, your order is ready.

281
00:22:51,800 --> 00:22:53,240
Thank you so much.

282
00:23:01,840 --> 00:23:02,920
A-Mah, are you hungry?

283
00:23:05,920 --> 00:23:09,600
[Day 3]

284
00:23:12,000 --> 00:23:13,840
Thank you so much.

285
00:23:14,160 --> 00:23:15,640
Welcome in.

286
00:23:16,120 --> 00:23:18,160
Hello, there. What can I get you?

287
00:23:21,840 --> 00:23:22,840
Just a moment, dear.

288
00:23:23,000 --> 00:23:24,080
Just a moment.

289
00:23:25,600 --> 00:23:26,320
Oh...

290
00:23:27,800 --> 00:23:28,520
Here you go.

291
00:23:29,000 --> 00:23:30,120
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

292
00:23:32,200 --> 00:23:33,960
Doesn't your arm hurt?

293
00:23:34,160 --> 00:23:35,160
It's a different arm.

294
00:23:36,060 --> 00:23:37,060
I hurt my right one.

295
00:23:38,760 --> 00:23:39,600
Okay.

296
00:23:41,560 --> 00:23:43,000
Here comes a customer.

297
00:23:43,040 --> 00:23:45,600
See? You're so good at sales.

298
00:23:45,640 --> 00:23:47,160
Just a moment, alright?

299
00:23:47,600 --> 00:23:48,840
She just started.

300
00:23:49,600 --> 00:23:51,040
Here you go.

301
00:23:52,040 --> 00:23:53,040
Here, dear.

302
00:23:53,160 --> 00:23:54,840
A-Mah, how about this?

303
00:23:54,960 --> 00:23:56,360
Let's lure some customers in.

304
00:23:56,520 --> 00:23:57,760
I even have a song just for this.

305
00:23:58,040 --> 00:23:59,240
Alright, what song?

306
00:23:59,280 --> 00:24:00,520
Sing along with me.

307
00:24:01,160 --> 00:24:03,120
♫Shio pan, shio pan♫

308
00:24:03,160 --> 00:24:03,880
That's how it goes.

309
00:24:04,280 --> 00:24:05,120
With the dances?

310
00:24:05,160 --> 00:24:06,760
Yes! Come on now.

311
00:24:06,800 --> 00:24:09,000
- ♫Shio pan, shio pan♫
- ♫Shio pan, shio pan♫

312
00:24:12,120 --> 00:24:13,680
I used to do this,

313
00:24:13,720 --> 00:24:15,200
and customers would pour in like crazy!

314
00:24:15,240 --> 00:24:17,760
- No doubt we're gonna make insane sales!
- True.

315
00:24:25,640 --> 00:24:28,360
So many customers today!

316
00:24:28,720 --> 00:24:30,320
I'm almost shattered to pieces.

317
00:24:31,120 --> 00:24:33,640
You couldn't typically stand
my company, could you?

318
00:24:34,380 --> 00:24:36,320
Suddenly, you took on such a burden.

319
00:24:36,560 --> 00:24:38,600
You must have been very uncomfortable.

320
00:24:39,440 --> 00:24:41,160
Jeez, A-Mah!

321
00:24:41,480 --> 00:24:43,920
You're not a burden.

322
00:24:44,480 --> 00:24:47,440
It's you who couldn't
stand my company, isn't it?

323
00:24:48,880 --> 00:24:52,000
Do you not love me

324
00:24:52,440 --> 00:24:53,680
because I'm a granddaughter?

325
00:24:54,480 --> 00:24:56,680
I love my grandchildren equally.

326
00:24:58,480 --> 00:25:00,040
It's because you are a woman,

327
00:25:01,120 --> 00:25:02,880
like I am a woman.

328
00:25:03,800 --> 00:25:04,800
I know too well

329
00:25:04,840 --> 00:25:06,920
how much harder it is for us women

330
00:25:07,440 --> 00:25:09,320
to achieve anything at all.

331
00:25:09,560 --> 00:25:12,160
We have to fight
ten times harder than men.

332
00:25:13,200 --> 00:25:14,200
So how could I

333
00:25:14,360 --> 00:25:18,880
bring up a granddaughter
like I did a grandson?

334
00:25:22,860 --> 00:25:24,240
But do you know that

335
00:25:25,240 --> 00:25:30,000
it's much different now
compared to when you were young?

336
00:25:30,920 --> 00:25:33,880
We women can do everything

337
00:25:33,920 --> 00:25:35,200
just like men can.

338
00:25:47,600 --> 00:25:48,800
Look at me.

339
00:25:49,320 --> 00:25:52,000
I run this business all alone.

340
00:25:52,040 --> 00:25:53,960
You name it, I do everything.

341
00:25:54,760 --> 00:25:57,000
But I've got your help today.

342
00:25:58,800 --> 00:25:59,800
You're right about that.

343
00:26:04,920 --> 00:26:05,920
Hold on, A-Mah.

344
00:26:08,400 --> 00:26:09,600
Hello, Uncle?

345
00:26:11,040 --> 00:26:13,280
Jane, I'm here. Come out.

346
00:26:14,240 --> 00:26:15,160
Okay.

347
00:26:18,720 --> 00:26:19,560
Come on, A-Mah.

348
00:26:19,600 --> 00:26:20,600
Uncle is here to pick you up.

349
00:26:20,760 --> 00:26:22,080
Even when picking me up,

350
00:26:22,800 --> 00:26:24,120
he refuses to get out of the car.

351
00:26:24,560 --> 00:26:26,280
The door is just right there,

352
00:26:26,320 --> 00:26:27,320
so why not come?

353
00:26:29,240 --> 00:26:30,840
Come on, A-Mah. It's alright.

354
00:26:31,360 --> 00:26:33,200
When you get bored,

355
00:26:33,560 --> 00:26:36,040
you can stop by to help me sell shio pan.

356
00:26:36,960 --> 00:26:38,640
You won't get paid, though.

357
00:26:40,080 --> 00:26:42,040
It's alright. I have plenty

358
00:26:42,680 --> 00:26:43,610
thanks to these arms.

359
00:26:45,580 --> 00:26:46,360
Let's go, A-Mah.

360
00:26:46,400 --> 00:26:47,400
- Alright.
- Let's go.

361
00:26:47,960 --> 00:26:50,280
Come back whenever you have time.

362
00:26:50,520 --> 00:26:52,880
- Help me with the sales.
- Alright, alright.

363
00:27:15,240 --> 00:27:16,840
The sales aren't too shabby at all.

364
00:27:34,880 --> 00:27:38,080
Today, I won A-Mah's heart.

365
00:27:38,760 --> 00:27:39,600
How did I do?

366
00:27:40,220 --> 00:27:41,120
Good?

367
00:27:50,680 --> 00:27:51,600
Here.

368
00:27:52,000 --> 00:27:54,400
I made you a small one.

369
00:28:15,240 --> 00:28:16,320
There's a hair clip to go with it.

370
00:28:27,920 --> 00:28:29,080
That's adorable.

371
00:28:42,200 --> 00:28:44,000
I wish you were here with me...

372
00:29:07,040 --> 00:29:08,040
All done.

373
00:29:09,360 --> 00:29:13,040
Wow, you're all dolled up!

374
00:29:14,080 --> 00:29:15,520
May you make great sales today, dear.

375
00:29:15,840 --> 00:29:17,340
Sadhu!

376
00:29:17,520 --> 00:29:18,280
Abracadabra!

377
00:29:21,280 --> 00:29:23,200
I'll have to thank you

378
00:29:23,560 --> 00:29:26,280
for buying me three ovens.

379
00:29:26,320 --> 00:29:27,560
What a rich girl move.

380
00:29:32,880 --> 00:29:33,800
Thank you so much.

381
00:29:34,760 --> 00:29:36,240
Here you go.

382
00:29:37,560 --> 00:29:39,040
Let me go deliver the customer's orders.

383
00:29:39,320 --> 00:29:40,120
I'll be back.

384
00:29:41,880 --> 00:29:43,440
Please take care
of the shop and A-Mah while I'm gone.

385
00:29:43,480 --> 00:29:44,280
Sure thing.

386
00:29:44,880 --> 00:29:45,600
I'll be back.

387
00:29:46,240 --> 00:29:47,320
Be safe.

388
00:29:47,360 --> 00:29:48,560
I'll be right back.

389
00:29:51,640 --> 00:29:52,880
Here you go.

390
00:29:53,000 --> 00:29:54,200
Thank you so much.

391
00:29:54,240 --> 00:29:55,640
Enjoy your bread.

392
00:29:57,600 --> 00:29:59,880
Help me! Someone stole my purse!

393
00:29:59,920 --> 00:30:01,640
Give it back!

394
00:30:17,640 --> 00:30:18,440
Z!

395
00:30:32,800 --> 00:30:34,360
Excuse me, excuse me...

396
00:30:37,760 --> 00:30:38,960
Mission complete.

397
00:30:40,440 --> 00:30:41,360
Thank you.

398
00:30:42,240 --> 00:30:43,080
Thank you.

399
00:31:52,120 --> 00:31:54,320
[Song Wat]

400
00:32:08,400 --> 00:32:09,240
Z!

401
00:32:37,220 --> 00:32:38,500
Where have you been?

402
00:32:42,800 --> 00:32:44,120
I couldn't miss you more.

403
00:32:48,520 --> 00:32:49,680
Who are you, Miss?

404
00:32:51,000 --> 00:32:52,040
Do we know each other?

405
00:32:53,520 --> 00:32:54,400
What?!

406
00:32:54,680 --> 00:32:55,800
It's Jane!

407
00:32:56,600 --> 00:32:57,440
Jane!

408
00:33:00,200 --> 00:33:01,640
Are you messing with me?

409
00:33:01,680 --> 00:33:03,200
I noticed it from earlier, too.

410
00:33:03,600 --> 00:33:04,640
Don't play.

411
00:33:04,920 --> 00:33:05,920
I can see right through you.

412
00:33:06,840 --> 00:33:07,520
Huh?

413
00:33:10,360 --> 00:33:12,000
What?! You...

414
00:33:12,620 --> 00:33:14,400
You lived with me for a long time,

415
00:33:14,520 --> 00:33:16,200
we baked every day,

416
00:33:16,480 --> 00:33:18,640
and we even hung out at Song Wat!

417
00:33:23,240 --> 00:33:24,360
I'm sorry,

418
00:33:24,560 --> 00:33:25,800
but I think...

419
00:33:26,080 --> 00:33:27,680
you got the wrong person.

420
00:33:55,320 --> 00:33:56,840
She really doesn't remember me?

421
00:34:03,040 --> 00:34:06,320
Welcome, Jane,
to the Lucky Points system.

422
00:34:09,320 --> 00:34:12,600
I wish for Angel Z to come back to me.

423
00:34:12,639 --> 00:34:14,520
[A longing wish:
Please specify three wishes]

424
00:34:20,760 --> 00:34:21,840
- Ta-da!
- What?!

425
00:34:24,239 --> 00:34:25,239
Who are you?

426
00:34:26,600 --> 00:34:28,120
I'm a Z-ranked angel.

427
00:34:28,280 --> 00:34:29,880
You asked for me.

428
00:34:31,360 --> 00:34:32,360
This isn't right.

429
00:34:32,840 --> 00:34:34,000
I didn't ask for you!

430
00:34:34,360 --> 00:34:38,199
I meant Angel Z, who's a girl.

431
00:34:39,000 --> 00:34:40,120
And...

432
00:34:41,370 --> 00:34:44,409
she's blonde.

433
00:34:44,600 --> 00:34:47,080
Ugh, there are
so many angels in this rank.

434
00:34:47,639 --> 00:34:49,480
Just hurry up
and tell me what you need my help with.

435
00:34:57,440 --> 00:34:58,640
What? Uncle!

436
00:34:59,260 --> 00:35:00,560
My points are gone!

437
00:35:01,280 --> 00:35:03,280
Of course, you just made a wish.

438
00:35:04,400 --> 00:35:05,200
In that case,

439
00:35:06,600 --> 00:35:07,760
I'm sorry, Uncle.

440
00:35:08,360 --> 00:35:10,360
Jeez, Uncle this, Uncle that.

441
00:35:16,480 --> 00:35:17,360
Uncle!

442
00:35:18,200 --> 00:35:20,840
I wish to meet all the Z-ranked angels.

443
00:35:22,240 --> 00:35:23,680
Come on in!

444
00:35:42,200 --> 00:35:44,160
Is this everyone in the Z rank?

445
00:35:44,600 --> 00:35:45,920
Yes, we have everyone here.

446
00:35:46,120 --> 00:35:51,200
Well, what about
a girl with short blonde hair?

447
00:35:51,680 --> 00:35:53,760
The one who's a ball
of cuteness, you know?

448
00:35:54,000 --> 00:35:56,200
Oh, that kinda rings a bell.

449
00:35:56,240 --> 00:35:57,840
But it seems like she has moved,

450
00:35:57,880 --> 00:35:59,480
though I don't know if it's up or down.

451
00:36:02,280 --> 00:36:03,080
What?

452
00:36:05,320 --> 00:36:07,680
How can I ask for you back?

453
00:36:27,400 --> 00:36:29,240
I've tried all the wordings out there.

454
00:36:38,440 --> 00:36:42,400
I wish for the angel I love the most
to come spend forever with me.

455
00:36:42,440 --> 00:36:43,400
[Make a wish]

456
00:37:26,320 --> 00:37:27,240
Z?

457
00:37:53,920 --> 00:37:55,680
Ta-da!

458
00:37:56,520 --> 00:37:59,640
This is my very own shio pan shop!

459
00:38:02,600 --> 00:38:03,880
It's pretty nice.

460
00:38:07,240 --> 00:38:09,560
I told you

461
00:38:09,600 --> 00:38:11,720
that no matter what happened,
I'd open this shop.

462
00:38:14,200 --> 00:38:15,120
Remember?

463
00:38:27,640 --> 00:38:29,400
I took you here,

464
00:38:29,440 --> 00:38:30,760
and you still can't recall it?

465
00:38:36,580 --> 00:38:37,880
Not really.

466
00:38:45,080 --> 00:38:48,280
Did I say something wrong?

467
00:38:49,320 --> 00:38:50,320
Oh...

468
00:38:52,340 --> 00:38:53,340
You didn't.

469
00:38:54,320 --> 00:38:55,320
Uh...

470
00:38:55,820 --> 00:38:57,480
So, did you take me here

471
00:38:57,880 --> 00:38:59,160
because you need my help?

472
00:38:59,680 --> 00:39:00,600
You can tell me.

473
00:39:02,280 --> 00:39:03,200
Well,

474
00:39:04,080 --> 00:39:05,880
just having you with me is enough.

475
00:39:13,400 --> 00:39:14,400
I guess?

476
00:39:28,080 --> 00:39:29,400
Hi!

477
00:39:31,480 --> 00:39:32,480
Auntie Bew.

478
00:39:33,400 --> 00:39:35,320
I just happened
to be running errands nearby,

479
00:39:35,480 --> 00:39:37,720
so I'm stopping by
to buy some desserts for my mom.

480
00:39:38,040 --> 00:39:39,680
Oh...

481
00:40:20,320 --> 00:40:21,240
Bew?

482
00:40:25,240 --> 00:40:26,240
No...

483
00:40:28,960 --> 00:40:29,960
Mom?

484
00:40:41,640 --> 00:40:43,440
Beam is finally back with us.

485
00:41:16,940 --> 00:41:18,080
What is it?

486
00:41:20,200 --> 00:41:21,200
Nothing.

487
00:41:26,920 --> 00:41:28,280
How do you feel?

488
00:41:29,960 --> 00:41:30,600
Hm?

489
00:41:32,480 --> 00:41:33,480
Well,

490
00:41:34,840 --> 00:41:36,760
I'm talking about
when you met Auntie Bew earlier.

491
00:41:40,120 --> 00:41:41,440
It felt nice.

492
00:41:42,040 --> 00:41:43,280
I reunited with my mom after all.

493
00:41:46,800 --> 00:41:49,240
And since you remember her,

494
00:41:50,440 --> 00:41:51,360
what about me?

495
00:41:51,680 --> 00:41:52,680
Do you finally know who I am?

496
00:41:59,000 --> 00:42:00,440
It doesn't really ring a bell...

497
00:42:07,760 --> 00:42:10,440
Well, try thinking long and hard.

498
00:42:11,000 --> 00:42:13,240
We used to be so, so close.

499
00:42:13,400 --> 00:42:15,240
You lived in my house,

500
00:42:15,280 --> 00:42:16,800
we talked every day,

501
00:42:17,160 --> 00:42:18,920
and we baked every day!

502
00:42:19,080 --> 00:42:20,480
It was so much fun!

503
00:42:20,760 --> 00:42:21,920
And...

504
00:42:22,320 --> 00:42:24,720
you liked lying down
and looking at my face.

505
00:42:24,760 --> 00:42:27,120
I loved dragging you around,

506
00:42:27,640 --> 00:42:28,800
and we...

507
00:42:30,200 --> 00:42:31,840
kissed so many times.

508
00:42:32,360 --> 00:42:33,240
That's enough.

509
00:42:36,200 --> 00:42:38,320
I don't think I'll remember it,
no matter how many times you say it.

510
00:42:39,840 --> 00:42:40,920
So just stop.

511
00:42:42,440 --> 00:42:43,520
It's making me uncomfortable.

512
00:43:08,760 --> 00:43:10,360
Do you really want me to share the bed?

513
00:43:13,120 --> 00:43:13,800
Mm.

514
00:43:17,160 --> 00:43:17,960
I forgot...

515
00:43:18,720 --> 00:43:19,600
Then...

516
00:43:21,060 --> 00:43:22,060
Just pick wherever.

517
00:43:49,840 --> 00:43:50,720
Z!

518
00:43:53,600 --> 00:43:54,760
Did you remove the apron?

519
00:43:55,160 --> 00:43:55,840
Mm.

520
00:43:57,360 --> 00:43:58,440
Why?

521
00:43:59,640 --> 00:44:01,560
Well, it was weird to see,

522
00:44:01,880 --> 00:44:02,760
so I did.

523
00:44:18,800 --> 00:44:20,760
I'm gonna make you some breakfast.

524
00:44:22,800 --> 00:44:23,800
I'm not gonna stop.

525
00:44:30,760 --> 00:44:32,720
Yesterday, you told me to stop.

526
00:44:33,560 --> 00:44:34,560
I refused.

527
00:44:35,440 --> 00:44:36,200
Huh?

528
00:44:37,480 --> 00:44:39,400
I used a hundred thousand points
to redeem you back,

529
00:44:39,920 --> 00:44:41,040
so why should I stop?

530
00:44:41,080 --> 00:44:42,080
I'm not gonna stop!

531
00:44:44,080 --> 00:44:45,000
Listen.

532
00:44:45,820 --> 00:44:47,480
Whatever I tell you to do,

533
00:44:47,520 --> 00:44:48,640
you have to do it.

534
00:44:49,200 --> 00:44:51,320
If I tell you to remember me,

535
00:44:51,360 --> 00:44:52,720
you have to remember me!

536
00:45:16,520 --> 00:45:17,520
Hey!

537
00:45:17,800 --> 00:45:19,840
Every day, this was how
you kneaded the dough.

538
00:45:20,120 --> 00:45:20,960
Remember?

539
00:45:23,880 --> 00:45:24,640
Look,

540
00:45:25,160 --> 00:45:27,120
this is my special shio pan recipe.

541
00:45:29,800 --> 00:45:30,520
Here.

542
00:45:36,240 --> 00:45:37,000
What do you think?

543
00:45:37,680 --> 00:45:39,080
Does the taste ring a bell?

544
00:45:43,960 --> 00:45:44,760
No.

545
00:45:57,240 --> 00:45:58,360
Try listening to this.

546
00:46:01,800 --> 00:46:07,440
♫You secretly got my head in the clouds♫

547
00:46:07,880 --> 00:46:13,240
♫Your smile almost got me on the ground♫

548
00:46:13,280 --> 00:46:14,200
Come on.

549
00:46:15,760 --> 00:46:17,160
Sing it for me.

550
00:46:19,640 --> 00:46:20,880
It's the first time I've ever heard it.

551
00:46:21,440 --> 00:46:22,440
I don't think I can.

552
00:46:28,920 --> 00:46:29,600
Look,

553
00:46:30,540 --> 00:46:33,400
remember where we used to hang out?

554
00:46:45,160 --> 00:46:46,320
No...

555
00:46:53,280 --> 00:46:55,600
We used to lounge right here.

556
00:46:58,720 --> 00:46:59,720
And you...

557
00:47:01,400 --> 00:47:02,680
rested your head on my shoulder like so.

558
00:47:07,920 --> 00:47:09,200
And we...

559
00:47:10,280 --> 00:47:11,560
took photos like this.

560
00:47:14,080 --> 00:47:15,120
It's just like last year.

561
00:47:17,600 --> 00:47:18,400
Look.

562
00:47:22,060 --> 00:47:24,040
Can you remember it?

563
00:47:39,200 --> 00:47:40,000
Okay,

564
00:47:40,880 --> 00:47:41,680
it's fine.

565
00:47:45,920 --> 00:47:47,080
Let's hold hands like so.

566
00:47:47,840 --> 00:47:49,080
Jump in sync with me.

567
00:47:51,040 --> 00:47:51,680
Let's go.

568
00:47:53,280 --> 00:47:54,120
Okay!

569
00:47:56,960 --> 00:47:58,240
And...

570
00:48:12,280 --> 00:48:13,480
Come here.

571
00:48:30,560 --> 00:48:31,440
Z,

572
00:48:32,720 --> 00:48:33,720
do you remember it now?

573
00:48:42,880 --> 00:48:44,080
I'm sorry, Jane.

574
00:48:53,240 --> 00:48:54,000
Mm.

575
00:48:56,360 --> 00:48:57,360
It's fine.

576
00:48:59,560 --> 00:49:02,480
Just... take it slow.

577
00:49:03,040 --> 00:49:05,160
I'm sure it'll come back.

578
00:49:20,280 --> 00:49:22,040
Then, tomorrow,

579
00:49:22,340 --> 00:49:24,280
I'll take you
to more places we used to go

580
00:49:24,400 --> 00:49:25,560
in case you recall anything.

581
00:49:27,480 --> 00:49:28,200
Mm.

582
00:49:32,440 --> 00:49:33,520
[Music rehearsal room, third floor]

583
00:50:10,720 --> 00:50:12,320
There's no reason to try anymore.

584
00:50:21,440 --> 00:50:22,280
Come here!

585
00:50:31,960 --> 00:50:33,680
Whoa, Z!

586
00:50:38,360 --> 00:50:39,160
Z...

587
00:50:49,080 --> 00:50:50,080
Are you okay?

588
00:50:51,720 --> 00:50:52,720
Are you hurt?

589
00:50:54,000 --> 00:50:55,240
Does your head still hurt?

590
00:51:05,360 --> 00:51:06,280
Jane...

591
00:51:16,800 --> 00:51:17,800
Don't tell me...

592
00:51:20,000 --> 00:51:20,880
that you...

593
00:51:27,160 --> 00:51:28,240
I remember everything.

594
00:51:32,840 --> 00:51:34,720
I remember everything about us, Jane.

595
00:51:50,160 --> 00:51:51,280
I'm so happy...

596
00:52:34,800 --> 00:52:35,560
Right?

597
00:52:40,440 --> 00:52:41,880
Congrats!

598
00:52:42,000 --> 00:52:44,640
Finally, your memory came back.

599
00:52:45,120 --> 00:52:46,280
- Ate!
- Ate!

600
00:52:46,560 --> 00:52:47,560
Congrats!

601
00:52:47,920 --> 00:52:49,000
Look at her.

602
00:52:49,160 --> 00:52:50,830
I guess she's even happier than you,

603
00:52:50,920 --> 00:52:52,400
judging from that silly grin!

604
00:52:53,120 --> 00:52:54,060
- Auntie Itt!
- Ooh!

605
00:52:58,840 --> 00:52:59,760
Adorable couple, aren't they?

606
00:53:00,720 --> 00:53:01,120
Argh!!

607
00:53:01,160 --> 00:53:01,680
- Eek!
- Whoa!

608
00:53:01,720 --> 00:53:03,120
- Wait a minute...
- Ugh!

609
00:53:03,160 --> 00:53:04,240
- What?
- What was that?

610
00:53:04,480 --> 00:53:06,000
Since her memory is back,

611
00:53:06,040 --> 00:53:08,080
wouldn't this be another punishable violation?

612
00:53:08,600 --> 00:53:09,360
- You're right.
- You have a point.

613
00:53:09,400 --> 00:53:10,400
- I didn't think about that...
- Argh...

614
00:53:10,440 --> 00:53:11,640
No way!!

615
00:53:12,680 --> 00:53:13,840
He has a point...

616
00:53:29,400 --> 00:53:31,400
No worries!

617
00:53:33,360 --> 00:53:34,480
- Uncle Duang!
- Uncle Duang!

618
00:53:36,720 --> 00:53:38,280
How's it hanging, Uncle?!

619
00:53:39,560 --> 00:53:43,480
Your memory coming back
this time around isn't a violation

620
00:53:43,660 --> 00:53:45,600
since it was force majeure.

621
00:53:46,040 --> 00:53:50,000
Not a single soul has the right
to take you in for punishment!

622
00:53:53,360 --> 00:53:54,160
Is this true?

623
00:53:54,280 --> 00:53:55,280
Are you punking me?

624
00:53:55,640 --> 00:53:57,560
It's nothing but the truth!

625
00:53:57,600 --> 00:53:58,720
Plus,

626
00:53:59,760 --> 00:54:02,520
I'm not the same old Duang-Jai anymore.

627
00:54:04,460 --> 00:54:05,560
Why not?

628
00:54:13,840 --> 00:54:14,680
What's that?

629
00:54:16,180 --> 00:54:20,000
Right now, I have taken over
Miss Kaew-Ta's position!

630
00:54:20,160 --> 00:54:22,320
I guarantee that
I'm a hundred times more kind-hearted!

631
00:54:22,360 --> 00:54:24,560
Don't worry, be happy!

632
00:54:24,600 --> 00:54:26,880
- Yay!
- Yay!

633
00:54:29,880 --> 00:54:30,880
Don't worry.

634
00:54:33,080 --> 00:54:34,080
Uhh, who's that?

635
00:54:35,080 --> 00:54:36,080
Jane?

636
00:54:36,600 --> 00:54:37,600
Jane, sweetie?

637
00:54:38,280 --> 00:54:39,360
Who is he?

638
00:54:43,160 --> 00:54:45,680
I'm Duang-Jai,
the new leader of the angels.

639
00:54:45,880 --> 00:54:47,720
- Ooh!
- Right!

640
00:54:47,760 --> 00:54:51,040
I never knew that angels...

641
00:54:51,200 --> 00:54:52,800
- look like this.
- Right?

642
00:54:52,840 --> 00:54:54,120
He kinda looks like that one singer.

643
00:54:54,160 --> 00:54:55,320
He's totally your type, girl!

644
00:54:55,560 --> 00:54:57,080
Doesn't he look like Joke So Cool?

645
00:54:57,120 --> 00:54:58,720
He looks just like him!

646
00:54:58,960 --> 00:54:59,960
- Ooh!
- Isn't he?

647
00:55:03,600 --> 00:55:04,880
Here's your drink.

648
00:55:17,160 --> 00:55:21,280
[I want to die]

649
00:55:27,680 --> 00:55:28,920
I didn't order that.

650
00:55:29,560 --> 00:55:31,160
It's a special gift from us.

651
00:55:33,160 --> 00:55:34,720
Our shio pan

652
00:55:35,040 --> 00:55:37,640
can literally warm your entire heart.

653
00:55:37,960 --> 00:55:40,280
Anytime you don't feel your best,

654
00:55:41,280 --> 00:55:43,400
try filling your stomach
with something yummy

655
00:55:44,160 --> 00:55:45,800
and take a little nap.

656
00:55:46,680 --> 00:55:48,840
That might just make you feel that

657
00:55:49,240 --> 00:55:54,840
living in this world
is the most valuable gift out there.

658
00:56:01,560 --> 00:56:02,800
Enjoy your dessert.

659
00:56:09,800 --> 00:56:14,400
I introduce you to
'Six-Degrees Shio Pan Set'!

660
00:56:15,680 --> 00:56:17,520
This is the first degree,

661
00:56:17,840 --> 00:56:20,880
an avocado-filled shio pan.

662
00:56:20,920 --> 00:56:24,520
This was inspired by the moment
we filmed the MV with Miss Clare.

663
00:56:24,760 --> 00:56:27,960
- It tastes a little astringent, salty,
- You're gonna act funny to win her back!

664
00:56:28,000 --> 00:56:28,920
and tart...

665
00:56:29,360 --> 00:56:30,520
but all well-balanced.

666
00:56:32,200 --> 00:56:34,120
The second-degree shio pan

667
00:56:34,160 --> 00:56:35,560
is one with pineapple and kimchi filling.

668
00:56:35,860 --> 00:56:37,960
That sounds... odd.

669
00:56:38,280 --> 00:56:40,160
It was inspired by our meeting with Tom.

670
00:56:40,200 --> 00:56:42,560
Remember? Master Satanfah

671
00:56:42,760 --> 00:56:44,800
was both chaotic and messy,

672
00:56:45,120 --> 00:56:47,640
like these two ingredients
that don't supposedly seem to go well

673
00:56:48,160 --> 00:56:49,680
but surprisingly do.

674
00:56:50,200 --> 00:56:52,760
- When fate smiles on you, luck favors you!
- When fate smiles on you, luck favors you!

675
00:56:53,540 --> 00:56:55,760
Up next is the third degree.

676
00:56:55,920 --> 00:56:58,400
It's shio pan
with brownie and dark chocolate.

677
00:56:58,760 --> 00:57:01,200
This was when we spent the night
with the ghost for Pai!

678
00:57:03,080 --> 00:57:04,280
I was scared to death,

679
00:57:04,840 --> 00:57:07,720
but in the end, we curled up together,

680
00:57:09,880 --> 00:57:13,680
just like the bittersweet taste
this chocolate has to offer.

681
00:57:14,080 --> 00:57:15,400
What about the fourth degree?

682
00:57:15,860 --> 00:57:17,960
Shio pan with smoked salmon filling

683
00:57:18,000 --> 00:57:20,040
inspired by when we met Tony.

684
00:57:20,520 --> 00:57:24,480
I was really happy
that I got to sing on that stage,

685
00:57:24,720 --> 00:57:26,200
so I picked salmon

686
00:57:26,520 --> 00:57:30,160
because it's my favorite in the world!

687
00:57:31,480 --> 00:57:32,600
Totally biased!

688
00:57:34,520 --> 00:57:37,200
This is the fifth degree,

689
00:57:37,500 --> 00:57:39,640
coffee-almond-filled shio pan.

690
00:57:40,120 --> 00:57:42,240
Do you remember
when we met up with my mom?

691
00:57:42,680 --> 00:57:43,440
Mm-hm.

692
00:57:44,040 --> 00:57:46,600
That was such a bitter moment.

693
00:57:47,560 --> 00:57:48,800
I could only feel my tears.

694
00:57:49,400 --> 00:57:51,760
But I'm glad that I truly found her.

695
00:57:53,120 --> 00:57:55,040
Then what about the sixth degree?

696
00:57:55,240 --> 00:57:57,800
Shio pan with strawberry
and whipped cream filling.

697
00:57:58,120 --> 00:58:00,600
Sweet and heavenly,

698
00:58:01,440 --> 00:58:02,440
just like our relationship.

699
00:58:05,980 --> 00:58:07,960
My sixth degree

700
00:58:08,280 --> 00:58:09,400
is you.

701
00:58:10,900 --> 00:58:12,560
And your sixth degree

702
00:58:12,960 --> 00:58:13,960
is me.

703
00:58:18,280 --> 00:58:19,520
Therefore,

704
00:58:20,560 --> 00:58:22,440
this shio pan

705
00:58:23,240 --> 00:58:25,200
will embody our love.

706
00:58:30,400 --> 00:58:31,560
I love you, Z.

707
00:58:34,560 --> 00:58:35,880
I love you, too, Jane.

708
00:59:21,320 --> 00:59:23,040
Three, two, one!

709
00:59:31,640 --> 00:59:32,720
You're so cute.

710
00:59:36,600 --> 00:59:38,000
Love is reeking in the air!

711
00:59:47,480 --> 00:59:49,800
What are you looking at, singles?

712
00:59:50,400 --> 00:59:52,440
- Wow!
- Whoa!

713
00:59:52,920 --> 00:59:54,040
Alright!
